# Documentation Rules

## Required documentation for

- Public shared APIs
- Flutter–Unity protocol changes
- Firestore schema changes
- Security-rule changes
- New Cloud Functions
- New environment variables and secrets (names only in Git; values in Secret Manager)
- New deployment commands
- Breaking changes, game integration requirements, build publication changes
- Data migrations, new error codes, new analytics events

## Locations

| Topic | Path |
|-------|------|
| Product rules | `docs/product/` |
| Architecture | `docs/architecture/` |
| Development | `docs/development/` |
| Testing | `docs/testing/` |
| Operations | `docs/operations/` |
| Game integration | `docs/game_integration/` |
| Prompts | `docs/prompts/` |

## Code comments

Explain **why**, constraints, non-obvious decisions, security assumptions, compatibility behaviour. Do not repeat obvious code.

Good: *Use the locally displayed score only for gameplay feedback. The backend recalculates result eligibility before ranking.*

## README requirements (major modules)

Purpose, responsibilities, dependencies, setup, testing, limitations, ownership, related documents.

## Pull requests

Update relevant README, architecture doc, protocol changelog, schema doc, and release notes as applicable.

## Review checklist

- [ ] Behavioural changes documented
- [ ] Protocol/schema docs updated if changed
- [ ] No secrets in documentation examples
